Advanced Mockito Use Cases
    🔹 1. doReturn vs when (TRICKY):
          when(obj.method()).thenReturn(val); // normal
         ⚠️ Problem with Spy: doReturn(val).when(obj).method(); // safer
            Use doReturn when: Using @Spy  and Avoid real method execution
    🔹 2. doThrow():
          doThrow(new RuntimeException())
              .when(repo).save(any());
    🔹 3. doAnswer() (Dynamic Logic):
        when(repo.save(any())).thenAnswer(invocation -> {
            User user = invocation.getArgument(0);
            user.setName("Modified");
            return user;
        });
     Powerful for:  Custom behavior and  Modifying input/output
    🔹 4. Argument Matchers
        when(repo.findById(anyInt())).thenReturn(user);
        Common:
            any()
            anyString()
            eq(value)
        ⚠️ Rule:
            when(repo.findById(1)).thenReturn(user); // OK
            when(repo.findById(anyInt())).thenReturn(user); // OK
            ❌ Mixing:when(repo.findById(anyInt(), "abc")) ❌ -> Must use all matchers or none
    🔹 5. verify() :
          verify(repo).findById(1);
         Advanced Verify:
          verify(repo, times(2)).save(any());
          verify(repo, never()).delete(any());
          verify(repo, atLeastOnce()).findAll();
    🔹 6. verifyNoInteractions():
          verifyNoInteractions(repo);
    🔹 7. InOrder Verification:
